**Bottom line:** The biggest win is making the constructor store only `Bits` (one division per construction instead of five), and rewriting `ToString` to select a value/symbol pair without `Replace` chains. For thousands of concurrent transfers updating per-second, this eliminates ~5 allocations per format call and ~4 redundant divisions per construction.
